This paper deals with techniques for analyzing and summarizing provenance data, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on graph analysis and data aggregation suggests that cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses outlier detection and conformance checking, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. The use of provenance data for visualization suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the proposed technique, which is relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
